it.emarolab.owloop.core

Class Axiom.EntitySet.SynchronisationIntent<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.emarolab.owloop.core.Axiom.EntitySet.SynchronisationIntent<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of entities described in an Axiom.EntitySet set. It should be the same parameter (or an extension) used for a specific Axiom.EntitySet implementation.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Axiom.ExpressionEntitySet.SynchronisationMultiIntent
    Enclosing interface:
    Axiom.EntitySet<Y>

    public static class Axiom.EntitySet.SynchronisationIntent<E>
extends java.lang.Object
    The synchronising intent during reading or writing of Axiom.EntitySet.

    It describes the changes that should be performed in a Axiom.EntitySet set or in an OWL ontology during: Axiom.Descriptor.readExpressionAxioms() or Axiom.Descriptor.writeExpressionAxioms(). This implementation considers sets of Axiom.EntitySet as a HashSet E.
    This class is not directly instantiable but it can be assessed through: EntitySet#synchroniseFrom(EntitySet) or EntitySet#synchroniseTo(EntitySet).

        public java.util.Set<E> getToAdd()
        Returns the element to add to the set in order to synchronise them. During Axiom.Descriptor.writeExpressionAxioms() those are the axioms to add in the OWL representation. During Axiom.Descriptor.readExpressionAxioms() those are the axioms to add to the OWLOOP representation.
        Returns:
        the element to add for synchronise the axioms sets.

        Returns:
        the element to add for synchronise the axioms sets.
